 and the chance to work together on this.</span><span style=3D"font-size:1.0=
pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:white">=E2=80=8A</span><o:=
p></o:p></p>
</div>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Good morning Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you so much for your email and for s=
haring the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devo=
nport. I really appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the chan=
ce to work together on this. It=E2=80=99s
 great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidance on how w=
e can move forward smoothly.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map a=
nd have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially around safety=
 and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about significant fire d=
amage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought
 to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me concerned ab=
out the house=E2=80=99s condition.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could we please consider the following adj=
ustments?<o:p></o:p></p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0cm" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1"><strong><span sty=
le=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Clarify Claim Scope</span></=
strong>: Is this the plan for both house and contents claims? If so, should i=
t therefore be linked to both policy numbers
 to ensure all coverage is included?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmsonormal"=
 style=3D"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1"><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;=
Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Prioritize Health &amp; Safety</span></strong>: I=E2=
=80=99d feel more comfortable if we scheduled independent assessments (elect=
rical, structural, gas, moisture/mould)
 before any major work, alongside the July 9 asbestos survey. The master ele=
ctrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is uninhabitable due to electri=
cal hazards is a key concern.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D=
"mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1"><strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quo=
t;,sans-serif">Assessment-Only Focus</span></strong>: As previously expresse=
d, could we limit initial tasks to enabling damage assessment (e.g., securin=
g the site,
 debris removal) rather than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination, curtai=
n cleaning)? This would allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual agreement=
 on remediation. The planned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels premature f=
or these reasons:
<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0cm" type=3D"disc">
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0cm" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2">We need to assess=
 damage before repair to preserve evidence.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmso=
normal" style=3D"mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2">If the gas unit (likely damaged) r=
equires removal, the ceiling may need cutting, necessitating re-cleaning.<o:=
p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2">The e=
lectrician=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work first.<o:=
p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l0 level2 lfo2">Fire=
fighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and electricity, which must be a=
ssessed and remediated.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso=
-list:l0 level2 lfo2">With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof w=
ork makes living there untenable until completed.<o:p></o:p></li></ol>
</ul>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0cm" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3"><strong><span sty=
le=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Asbestos Survey Details</spa=
n></strong>: While I=E2=80=99m supportive of the July 9 survey, could you pl=
ease share who will conduct it, the scope and tests involved,
 and how I can independently verify the results? Also, can the funding for t=
his be covered under the claim preparation provision?<o:p></o:p></li><li cla=
ss=3D"xmsonormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3"><strong><span style=3D"f=
ont-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Structural Engineer Guidelines</spa=
n></strong>: I previously asked about guidelines for paying a structural eng=
ineer, as per the provision for claim
 preparation. Could you please provide these, as I believe an independent as=
sessment should precede any repair work?<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could provi=
de a revised plan with a written timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occupa=
tion only after safety is assured, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025. I=
=E2=80=99m really looking forward to working with
 you for a safe and fair outcome.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella del Prete<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<div>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt">
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal">On 7 Jul 2025, at 5:31<span style=3D"font-family:&qu=
ot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">=E2=80=AF</span>PM, Grant Metson &lt;<a href=3D"m=
ailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt; wrote:<o:p>=
</o:p></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Good evening Rafael=
la,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thank you for takin=
g the time to meet with me last week.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">As discussed, pleas=
e find attached a process document which outlines the framework of how Tower=
 Insurance will progress your claim.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">This is a framework=
 only and the process will change, as we move through each step, given that f=
indings and results will affect the next step in the process. This will be a=
 live document that will gather
 detail as we progress.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">However, I do trust=
 that this will give you some insight and knowledge to allow us to participa=
te in the process together.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I look forward to s=
peaking with you soon.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please confirm back=
 via email when you get a chance that you agree for Asset Restore to underta=
ke the asbestos survey on the 9<sup>th</sup><span class=3D"xxapple-converted=
-space">&nbsp;</span>=E2=80=93 as this is the first
 step in the process.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"xmsonormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Regards,</span><o:p=
></o:p></p>
